      • create

        @NotNull
public static <L extends Label> @NotNull LabelIndex<L> create​(@NotNull
                                                              @NotNull java.util.List<L> labels)
        Creates a distinct (not capable of handling overlapping labels) label index.

        The technical definition of distinctness is that all labels should be able to be ordered such that start indices and end indices are strictly increasing.

        Type Parameters:
        L - The label type.
        Parameters:
        labels - Label objects to use to create the label index.
        Returns:
        Label Index object.

      • isDistinct

        public boolean isDistinct()
        Description copied from interface: LabelIndex
        Returns whether or not the index is distinct.

        Index distinctness is based on whether the labels in the index can overlap or cannot overlap. In the case of distinct, non-overlapping labels optimization can be made to the process of searching for labels, as well as iteration over and size computation of sub-indices.

        Returns:
        Returns true if the index is distinct, false if the index is not distinct.
